## Tool conventions

{% include 'tool-conventions.md' %}

## What to populate

- `sections` — per tool-conventions.md (typically a single
  numbered Steps section).
- `files` — `scripts/*` (executable + helpers) plus any
  `references/*.md`.
- `cli_surface` — optional. Populate when the skill ships a
  main shim.
- `rationale` — script layout, single-vs-split helpers,
  error-handling shape.

## Output construction

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task design

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task design \
    --set frontmatter.name=demo \
    --set frontmatter.type=tool \
    --set 'frontmatter.description=...' \
    --set 'sections[].heading=Steps' \
    --set 'sections[-1].outline=...' \
    --set 'files[].path=scripts/demo.sh' \
    --set 'files[-1].purpose=Main shim.' \
    --set 'files[-1].content_outline=...' \
    --set 'cli_surface[].command=run' \
    --set 'cli_surface[-1].args=<input>' \
    --set 'cli_surface[-1].description=Execute the tool on <input>.' \
    --set rationale='Script layout and error-handling tradeoffs...'
```

Syntax: `[]` appends, `[-1]` targets the last appended entry,
`.` nests.
